This is <b>Shaheer</b>, our featured citizen of the week!<br><br>Shaheer moved to <a href='/home/?user=shaheer11230'>29798-C Powder Horn Circle</a> on April 12, 2007, and since then he's been living it up. He spends most of his time playing sports of one kind or another. He's got the trophies to prove it. Shaheer has dominated in Sink Three, Rope Climb, Home Run Derby, the Peabody Park Half-Pipe and Kai's Surfari. <br><br>He is good at sports, but his skills with numbers aren't limited just to adding up the score. Shaheer has also mastered Sudoku. After all, athletes need to stay mentally sharp too.<br><br>With all of the amenities his house has to offer, Shaheer must enjoy living in his Westridge residence. If you're around, you can do some boxing training in Shaheer's workout room. When the gloves come off you can relax in his abode enjoying Shaheer's state-of-the-art sound system while he spins some music on his turntables.<br><br>Next time you see Shaheer, be sure to shake his hand and thank him for being such a great citizen.</div>
